WEBVTT

00:05.606 --> 00:07.439
- Who are you?
- My name is Quinlan,

00:07.441 --> 00:11.276
and you and I have something very
much in common. - What's that?

00:11.278 --> 00:14.847
- We are both
hunting the Master.

00:14.849 --> 00:16.382
-<i> The</i> Occido Lumen.

00:16.384 --> 00:18.951
<i> Somewhere in here is the key</i>

00:18.953 --> 00:21.320
<i> to the Master's demise.</i>
<i> I will use</i>

00:21.322 --> 00:23.122
<i> the book to end this plague.</i>

00:23.124 --> 00:25.657
- Abraham, how ironic

00:25.659 --> 00:27.459
that our duel should end
not with a fight,

00:27.461 --> 00:30.029
but with a simple
transaction in gold.

00:30.031 --> 00:33.065
- Both of you can bid it out. The
man with the deepest pocket wins.

00:33.067 --> 00:36.235
I guess this is yours, old man.
Congratulations.

00:36.237 --> 00:39.738
-<i> It seems Eldritch Palmer</i>
<i> would rather I have the book</i>

00:39.740 --> 00:42.341
than let it fall into
the hands of the Master.

00:42.343 --> 00:45.511
(applause)
- You folks are lucky.

00:45.513 --> 00:47.913
<i> You're on the last train out.</i>

00:47.915 --> 00:50.215
(train horn)

00:53.154 --> 00:55.154
- (Zack):<i> What just happened?</i>
- We've derailed.

00:55.156 --> 00:57.756
Zack!

00:57.758 --> 00:58.891
- Stop!

00:58.893 --> 01:01.093
- Argh! Ah!

01:01.095 --> 01:03.662
Zack!

01:05.166 --> 01:09.368
- Nora.
- She took him away with her.

01:09.370 --> 01:11.236
Don't!
- Nora.

01:11.238 --> 01:12.838
- It's done.

01:14.408 --> 01:16.942
(man screaming)

01:16.944 --> 01:20.345
- Zack is alive.
We want the<i> Lumen.</i>

01:20.347 --> 01:22.014
You have a choice
to make:

01:22.016 --> 01:25.284
the<i> Lumen</i> or Zack.

01:29.390 --> 01:31.256
- (man): Yeah. Can we get
some more of that culture

01:31.258 --> 01:33.625
in that slide there, please?

01:37.198 --> 01:39.264
(creature screaming)

01:41.202 --> 01:44.203
(creature growling)

01:52.213 --> 01:55.681
(indistinct talking)

02:14.602 --> 02:16.768
- Just make sure there's
no trace of the residue in it.

02:16.770 --> 02:18.770
- Yes, Doctor.

02:18.772 --> 02:21.340
- (man): Here are the reports.

02:21.342 --> 02:23.809
- Eight the hard way.
My lucky number.

02:23.811 --> 02:25.811
- I got a good feeling
about this batch.

02:25.813 --> 02:27.779
- I'll believe it
if you will.

02:27.781 --> 02:30.816
- Well, no one ever won a Nobel
without taking a risk.

02:30.818 --> 02:34.253
Using polio against
glioblastomas? That was one hell

02:34.255 --> 02:36.588
of a gamble. It paid off.
- Yeah, we're not winning

02:36.590 --> 02:38.991
a Nobel. We'll be lucky
if we don't end up in jail.

02:40.995 --> 02:43.362
(indistinct conversations)
(machine beeping regularly)

02:45.299 --> 02:47.866
- She's all set, Doctor.
- OK.

02:47.868 --> 02:49.968
The time is 03:00.

02:49.970 --> 02:53.005
We have just introduced
Extract 44

02:53.007 --> 02:56.475
intravenously into test
subject 5-0-5,

02:56.477 --> 02:59.344
a 72-year-old woman
with vascular dementia.

03:04.885 --> 03:08.153
- (woman): Pulse is increasing!
Now, 78.

03:08.155 --> 03:09.721
Temperature's ramping up.
- Keep an eye

03:09.723 --> 03:11.557
on her blood pressure.
- (woman): Yes, Doctor.

03:11.559 --> 03:14.960
(old woman moaning)

03:14.962 --> 03:17.196
- (woman): Tonic-clonic tremors.
This is not looking good.

03:17.198 --> 03:19.198
- (doctor): 300 milligrams
of labetalol!

03:19.200 --> 03:21.733
- Shit! She's spiking.
- Code Red!

03:21.735 --> 03:24.169
- We need an APAP IV in here,
stat! We've gotta get

03:24.171 --> 03:26.138
her temperature down.
- 2000 MIB. 2000 micrograms!

03:26.140 --> 03:27.873
Load her up and keep it coming!

03:27.875 --> 03:30.175
Get ready to breathe for her.
- She's going over.

03:30.177 --> 03:31.610
(fast beeping)

03:33.681 --> 03:35.414
- Move. Clear!
- Clear!

03:35.416 --> 03:36.982
(gunshot and long beep)

03:36.984 --> 03:39.051
♪ ♪

04:37.745 --> 04:41.380
- ♪♪ The man from the television
crawled into the train ♪

04:41.382 --> 04:43.382
♪ I wonder who he's gonna ♪

04:43.384 --> 04:46.418
♪ Stick it in this time ♪

04:46.420 --> 04:50.055
(indistinct conversations) ♪ Everyone
is looking for a little entertainment ♪

04:50.057 --> 04:53.258
♪ So they'll probably pull his hands off ♪
- We'll have, we'll have

04:53.260 --> 04:55.127
another round here!
- Our recovery team

04:55.129 --> 04:56.728
only found one
of their bodies.

04:56.730 --> 04:59.498
- You run into any<i> strigoi?</i>

04:59.500 --> 05:02.267
- Not a one.

05:02.269 --> 05:04.970
- The Master must have moved
his nesting spot.

05:04.972 --> 05:06.938
But now you know
he's here, right?

05:06.940 --> 05:09.508
So, when do we get
more troops?

05:11.445 --> 05:13.445
- Command's pulling out
of New York City.

05:13.447 --> 05:17.015
- The mission was to find
the King Rat!

05:17.017 --> 05:19.251
The King Muncher!
We found him!

05:19.253 --> 05:21.253
- I don't know what we found.
- Ah, come on.

05:21.255 --> 05:23.488
- I lost six good men
on those teams,

05:23.490 --> 05:25.557
and I got nothing
to show for it.

05:27.161 --> 05:29.628
They're cutting bait.
We're heading out.

05:29.630 --> 05:32.297
- To do what?

05:32.299 --> 05:34.466
- Try and control
the outbreak in D.C.

05:34.468 --> 05:36.835
The capitol falls;
the entire country does.

05:36.837 --> 05:39.604
- ♪ Things got back to normal as
the train began to roll again ♪

05:39.606 --> 05:42.140
- I can get you out
if you wanna come with us.

05:42.142 --> 05:45.210
- I got no desire to save D.C.

05:45.212 --> 05:47.279
- Yeah. I got that.

05:49.216 --> 05:51.817
Well...

05:51.819 --> 05:53.719
best of luck to you, Fet.

05:53.721 --> 05:56.121
- Yeah. You too.
- ♪ He'd like to go to Spain ♪

05:56.123 --> 05:58.623
♪ Or somewhere like that ♪

05:58.625 --> 06:00.892
♪ With his two-tone Bible
and his funny cigarettes ♪

06:00.894 --> 06:03.795
♪ His suntan lotion ♪

06:03.797 --> 06:05.964
♪ And his castanets ♪
- Another double.

06:05.966 --> 06:08.867
- I got it. - ♪ Waiting for
the end of the world ♪

06:08.869 --> 06:11.670
Another for me.
- (barman): Yes, ma'am!

06:11.672 --> 06:13.672
- SEALs are going
bye-bye, huh?

06:13.674 --> 06:16.641
- Yeah. Sad to say.
- ♪ Waiting through the end ♪

06:16.643 --> 06:18.643
- ♪ Of the world ♪

06:18.645 --> 06:21.246
- Have you noticed
these creatures

06:21.248 --> 06:24.516
are getting better? Faster?

06:24.518 --> 06:27.219
- They're learning
their environment, developing.

06:27.221 --> 06:29.755
- And they say
we're winning.

06:29.757 --> 06:31.757
- Well, it's pretty hard
to stamp out

06:31.759 --> 06:34.993
a bug that doubles its numbers
every couple of days, you know.

06:34.995 --> 06:36.862
- ♪ All got onto the train ♪

06:36.864 --> 06:38.764
- Councilwoman Faraldo
talks about

06:38.766 --> 06:42.033
how we're taking back this city.

06:42.035 --> 06:44.236
You and I are never
gonna see that day.

06:44.238 --> 06:46.905
Just like the song says.

06:46.907 --> 06:48.940
- An optimist, huh?

06:48.942 --> 06:51.510
- ♪ Hiding from a scandal
in the national press ♪

06:51.512 --> 06:53.512
♪ They had been trying
to get married ♪

06:53.514 --> 06:56.114
- Hmm... That's
why I'm making

06:56.116 --> 06:58.116
the glass half full turn empty.
- ♪ You may see them drowning ♪

06:58.118 --> 07:00.218
- ♪ As you stroll
along the beach ♪

07:00.220 --> 07:04.256
- (barman): Here you go.
- To tonight.

07:04.258 --> 07:05.957
All we got is this.

07:05.959 --> 07:08.427
- ♪ Waiting for the end
of the world ♪

07:08.429 --> 07:11.863
♪ Waiting for
the end of the world ♪

07:11.865 --> 07:13.198
(Fet growling)

07:13.200 --> 07:17.536
♪ Waiting to the end
of the world ♪

07:17.538 --> 07:20.439
♪ Waiting for
the end of the world ♪

07:21.975 --> 07:26.044
♪ Waiting for the end
of the world ♪

07:26.046 --> 07:29.214
♪ Waiting for
the end of the world ♪

07:29.216 --> 07:34.119
♪ Waiting for the end
of the world ♪

07:34.121 --> 07:37.355
♪ Waiting for
the end of the world ♪♪

07:40.494 --> 07:42.561
- Uh... Hmm.

07:42.563 --> 07:45.330
Need to go check
on my friends.

07:45.332 --> 07:47.332
- Hmm.

07:47.334 --> 07:50.268
It's, uh, Val, right?

07:50.270 --> 07:51.970
(sigh)

07:51.972 --> 07:54.272
- Vasiliy.

07:54.274 --> 07:57.075
And... Kathy, right?

07:57.077 --> 07:59.911
- Kate. It's close enough.

07:59.913 --> 08:01.980
- Yeah.
- Ha!

08:01.982 --> 08:04.249
- Uh...

08:04.251 --> 08:06.184
So, uh,

08:06.186 --> 08:08.720
see you later
tonight maybe?

08:10.023 --> 08:11.623
- Maybe.

08:11.625 --> 08:13.892
♪♪♪

08:23.437 --> 08:25.504
- Happy hunting.

08:30.310 --> 08:32.444
- (man on radio):<i> Last night,</i>
<i> the East Side Safe Zone</i>

08:32.446 --> 08:35.480
<i> suffered another incursion</i>
<i> at Lexington and East 75th.</i>

08:35.482 --> 08:38.550
<i> Critics of Councilwoman</i>
<i> Justine Faraldo point to this</i>

08:38.552 --> 08:41.887
<i> as yet another sign that her</i> <i> efforts
to secure the city</i> <i> are failing.</i>

08:41.889 --> 08:45.223
(gunfire)

08:45.225 --> 08:47.359
- (distant man):
Hurry up! It's coming!

08:49.663 --> 08:52.063
(siren)

08:52.065 --> 08:55.567
(gunshots)

09:02.075 --> 09:04.242
- (distant man): I want him
dead! Lead him in! Lead him in!

09:04.244 --> 09:06.244
(glass breaking)

09:06.246 --> 09:08.179
(gunshots)

09:08.181 --> 09:09.948
- (distant man): Wait!
Don't end it like that!

09:11.752 --> 09:14.853
- Hello?

09:14.855 --> 09:16.788
Fet?

09:20.494 --> 09:22.961
Professor Setrakian?

09:28.201 --> 09:30.235
Oof! Ugh!

09:30.237 --> 09:33.338
(low growling)
- How do you know the professor?

09:33.340 --> 09:35.807
- Let him go! He's a friend!

09:39.846 --> 09:41.513
(gasping)

09:43.450 --> 09:45.884
This is Dr. Ephraim
Goodweather.

09:45.886 --> 09:48.119
- What is this thing?

09:48.121 --> 09:51.690
- It's a long story,
but a good story.

09:51.692 --> 09:54.593
Come on.

09:58.265 --> 10:00.565
- All right.

10:00.567 --> 10:03.301
I am sitting down. Tell me.

10:09.142 --> 10:11.376
- Nora didn't make it.

10:22.756 --> 10:24.289
- How?

10:27.494 --> 10:30.095
- Our train never
got out of New York.

10:30.097 --> 10:32.097
<i> Strigoi,</i>
hundreds of them,

10:32.099 --> 10:34.733
they threw themselves
in front of the engine.

10:34.735 --> 10:36.935
It derailed.
It was chaos.

10:36.937 --> 10:39.170
I-I got separated

10:39.172 --> 10:41.239
from Zack and Nora.

10:42.976 --> 10:44.976
The whole thing was planned.

10:44.978 --> 10:47.145
It had to be.

10:47.147 --> 10:50.682
- Of course it was.

10:50.684 --> 10:54.185
- Kelly got to them
before I could.

10:54.187 --> 10:57.922
By the time I got to Nora,
she had been stung.

10:59.326 --> 11:03.094
She was turning, but she was
still conscious. She, uh...

11:06.133 --> 11:09.134
She ended it

11:09.136 --> 11:12.070
by touching her sword
to the third rail.

11:15.942 --> 11:17.942
- And your son?

11:17.944 --> 11:21.346
Did the mother turn him as well?
- I don't know.

11:21.348 --> 11:25.717
But Nora saw Kelly
taking him away.

11:25.719 --> 11:28.286
- (Fet): Without turning him?
Doesn't make any sense.

11:28.288 --> 11:30.622
Why would she do that?
- (Ephraim): I don't know.

11:32.693 --> 11:34.759
- Be careful, Ephraim.

11:36.496 --> 11:38.396
If she did not

11:38.398 --> 11:40.398
turn your son,
it can only mean

11:40.400 --> 11:44.369
the Master plans to use
the boy against you.

11:44.371 --> 11:46.371
- Why would he give
a shit about me?

11:46.373 --> 11:49.240
- You, you hurt him.

11:49.242 --> 11:52.444
You caused him a setback.
You defied him.

11:54.247 --> 11:57.482
I'm, uh...

11:57.484 --> 11:59.484
very sorry to hear

11:59.486 --> 12:01.486
about Dr. Martinez.

12:01.488 --> 12:05.023
She was, uh... She, uh...

12:05.025 --> 12:06.624
DAMN IT!

12:08.428 --> 12:10.161
- Here you go.

12:10.163 --> 12:12.764
Easy now. Easy now.

12:12.766 --> 12:15.734
That's it.
(siren blaring outside)

12:15.736 --> 12:18.336
Easy now.

12:35.188 --> 12:38.990
- I brought your things.
- You remembered.

12:44.297 --> 12:47.298
- We could read them together.

12:47.300 --> 12:49.033
Would you like that?

12:50.537 --> 12:53.404
- I guess.

12:53.406 --> 12:55.373
(sound of beating pulse)

12:55.375 --> 12:57.142
I want to get out

12:57.144 --> 12:59.644
of this room,
breathe some fresh air.

13:02.582 --> 13:05.116
- You will.

13:05.118 --> 13:08.486
Soon.
- It's what you always say,

13:08.488 --> 13:10.989
but it never happens.

13:21.401 --> 13:24.335
I miss Dad a lot.

13:24.337 --> 13:27.672
- The Master has a--
- Has a plan.

13:27.674 --> 13:30.041
I know, but you never say
what it is.

13:33.280 --> 13:36.114
- In time,

13:36.116 --> 13:38.483
you will see
we are all part of it.

13:38.485 --> 13:40.151
- Even Dad?

13:40.153 --> 13:42.687
- He has a role to play.

13:53.333 --> 13:55.333
(dog barking)

13:55.335 --> 13:58.002
(siren blaring)
- Hahaha!

14:00.707 --> 14:03.441
There it is,
boys and girls,

14:03.443 --> 14:05.443
Promised Land.

14:05.445 --> 14:07.378
- There are no
"Safe Street" placards.

14:07.380 --> 14:10.014
It means Faraldo's cops
haven't cleared it.

14:10.016 --> 14:12.784
- Yeah, but it's worth the risk.
My uncle was a major foodie.

14:12.786 --> 14:14.686
We'll be eating like kings.
- Have you guys

14:14.688 --> 14:16.888
raided a skyscraper before?
- Uh-uh.

14:16.890 --> 14:18.857
- What floor
is his place on?

14:18.859 --> 14:21.326
- 42nd.
(helicopter whirring)

14:21.328 --> 14:24.195
- If this place is infested,
then there may be

14:24.197 --> 14:25.964
42 floors of<i> strigoi</i>
between us and the street.

14:25.966 --> 14:28.499
This is stupid!
- Cleaned out everywhere else.

14:28.501 --> 14:30.969
If we don't take
bigger risks, we starve.

14:30.971 --> 14:32.637
(dog barking)

14:34.574 --> 14:37.976
- Good news is
that it's daylight.

14:37.978 --> 14:39.911
And that tower
has floor-to-ceiling windows.

14:39.913 --> 14:42.347
So we yank the drapes
as we move through it,

14:42.349 --> 14:45.583
blast the place with sunlight.
Stay out of the shadows.

14:45.585 --> 14:48.519
We get in and out before they
know we're there. Understood?

14:48.521 --> 14:51.990
- Mm-hmm.
- What the hell happened to you?

14:51.992 --> 14:54.759
Back when we were hacking together,
you didn't care about risks.

14:54.761 --> 14:57.161
- I was naive.

14:57.163 --> 14:59.163
- You were fearless.
- Yeah.

14:59.165 --> 15:02.166
Well, I'm not anymore.

15:02.168 --> 15:05.003
- Look, I know on some level,
this infection is apocalyptic,

15:05.005 --> 15:07.572
but... look at the upside.

15:09.209 --> 15:11.242
You and I used to talk
all the time about

15:11.244 --> 15:13.444
breaking the barriers between
the haves and the have-nots.

15:13.446 --> 15:16.614
It's happening, Dutch.

15:16.616 --> 15:18.616
The whole city is pressing
a restart button.

15:18.618 --> 15:21.719
- Oh, God! Are you
bloody kidding me, Braden?!

15:21.721 --> 15:24.122
Yeah, we used to talk a lot of
shit about changing the world,

15:24.124 --> 15:26.691
but what did we actually,
really accomplish?

15:26.693 --> 15:30.028
We screwed up the computers
of a few unscrupulous companies.

15:30.030 --> 15:32.030
Yeah, big wins.

15:32.032 --> 15:35.133
That is nothing compared to
what's happening now. Nothing!

15:35.135 --> 15:38.636
There is no restart button.

15:38.638 --> 15:40.872
The entire human race

15:40.874 --> 15:43.408
is circling
the drain.

15:43.410 --> 15:46.244
This isn't the beginning
of anything.

15:46.246 --> 15:48.713
Except maybe the end.

15:48.715 --> 15:50.915
♪♪♪

15:50.917 --> 15:52.917
(Braden sighs.)

15:52.919 --> 15:55.420
- We doing this?

15:55.422 --> 15:57.488
- Let's do this.
- Go.

16:02.462 --> 16:05.964
(gunshots and explosions)

16:05.966 --> 16:08.099
- (woman): You need to cancel
this meeting, sir.

16:08.101 --> 16:11.169
You're in no condition.
- Don't give me orders, dear.

16:11.171 --> 16:13.237
Ever.

16:13.239 --> 16:15.306
- Have I come at a bad time?

16:16.576 --> 16:18.443
- Not at all,
<i> Herr</i> Eichhorst.

16:18.445 --> 16:20.545
Please come in.

16:25.618 --> 16:28.086
- Well, she's certainly

16:28.088 --> 16:31.089
a change of pace for you.

16:31.091 --> 16:33.257
I miss Coco.

16:33.259 --> 16:36.594
I'm sure you do, too.

16:41.501 --> 16:43.434
- What's done is done.

16:43.436 --> 16:45.536
What can I do for you?
- Show me

16:45.538 --> 16:48.673
how many people,
precisely, have registered

16:48.675 --> 16:51.109
their blood types
at our Freedom Centers.

16:51.111 --> 16:53.578
- I have the figures
right here.

17:00.353 --> 17:02.820
- This is unacceptable.

17:02.822 --> 17:05.823
Our first two facilities
will be coming online soon.

17:05.825 --> 17:09.327
- Well, I can't force people
to submit to medical exams.

17:09.329 --> 17:11.162
- No, but Justine Faraldo can.

17:11.164 --> 17:13.898
- She does not
answer to me.

17:13.900 --> 17:15.500
- But you can influence her.

17:15.502 --> 17:18.569
She knows how important
the Freedom Centers are.

17:18.571 --> 17:22.640
Use that.
- I'll attend to it right away.

17:22.642 --> 17:24.976
(distant siren blaring)

17:30.250 --> 17:34.952
- Miriam's heart.
And Coco's next to it.

17:36.389 --> 17:40.258
So sentimental.

17:40.260 --> 17:43.327
Fitting in its own way.

17:43.329 --> 17:46.397
- Could you please
put it back! Argh!

17:46.399 --> 17:48.166
- Eldritch.

17:50.103 --> 17:52.336
Are you feeling all right?

17:55.275 --> 17:58.209
- Please, Eichhorst,

17:58.211 --> 18:00.278
I need the white.

18:02.215 --> 18:04.182
- Rewards must be earned.

18:04.184 --> 18:06.751
Your ego cost us
the<i> Occido Lumen.</i>

18:06.753 --> 18:09.387
If you want
the Master's white,

18:09.389 --> 18:13.057
you must prove that you have
learned your lesson.

18:13.059 --> 18:16.394
Find the Jew, retrieve the book.

18:16.396 --> 18:19.730
Only then will the Master
deign to consider

18:19.732 --> 18:21.699
your personal needs.

18:21.701 --> 18:23.968
- Of course,
that's only fair.

18:23.970 --> 18:26.003
- But frankly...

18:30.276 --> 18:33.611
...I wonder
about your sincerity.

18:33.613 --> 18:36.714
- I intend
to prove myself.

18:36.716 --> 18:40.351
- Yes. See that you do.

18:44.390 --> 18:46.657
(Ding!)

18:50.563 --> 18:52.964
- These condos used to go
for over 2 million a pop.

18:52.966 --> 18:55.399
- (whispering): Shh! No noise.

19:04.844 --> 19:07.044
♪♪♪

19:14.621 --> 19:16.420
Blinds first.

19:19.359 --> 19:20.691
(Beep!)

19:27.267 --> 19:29.500
- Come on!

19:31.304 --> 19:33.337
Please, please, please.

19:33.339 --> 19:35.173
Ha! Jackpot.

19:35.175 --> 19:37.308
- Jesus, look at all this stuff!
- (woman): Living room's

19:37.310 --> 19:40.044
clear.
- (Braden): Good.

19:40.046 --> 19:42.647
(siren blaring)

19:42.649 --> 19:44.549
Kimberly, Ron,

19:44.551 --> 19:47.451
check the bedroom.
(helicopter whirring)

19:47.453 --> 19:49.954
Yes! Yes!

20:02.368 --> 20:06.504
- Check under the bed.
- You check under the bed.

20:06.506 --> 20:08.439
- OK. And you get
the closet.

20:23.923 --> 20:25.723
(low growling)

20:29.562 --> 20:31.829
- Ron?

20:31.831 --> 20:33.598
Ron?

20:36.703 --> 20:37.802
(screaming)

20:39.772 --> 20:42.473
- Come on!

20:47.413 --> 20:49.413
(creature screaming)

20:51.384 --> 20:53.451
(creatures screaming)
and growling)

20:58.057 --> 20:59.624
Braden!

20:59.626 --> 21:01.993
- Ah!

21:07.734 --> 21:10.601
(Click!)
Ah!

21:10.603 --> 21:12.870
- Go! Go! Get out of here!

21:15.942 --> 21:17.942
(screaming and grunting)

21:34.761 --> 21:36.794
- Bastards!

21:42.001 --> 21:44.435
(growling)

21:44.437 --> 21:46.671
(Dutch gasping)

21:46.673 --> 21:49.340
Aah! Ugh!

21:49.342 --> 21:51.976
(creature screaming)

21:51.978 --> 21:54.412
AAH!
(creature screaming)

21:57.950 --> 21:59.950
(helicopter whirring)

21:59.952 --> 22:01.919
(distant indistinct yelling)

22:03.790 --> 22:07.591
(siren blaring)

22:07.593 --> 22:09.727
Oh.
(gasping)

22:16.302 --> 22:18.602
(sobbing)

22:34.620 --> 22:36.687
(car alarm system wailing)

22:38.558 --> 22:41.992
- 323 million dollars.

22:41.994 --> 22:44.895
- It got a little
out of hand.

22:44.897 --> 22:48.666
- We're still in
the early stages of translation.

22:48.668 --> 22:51.135
Much of this is written
in puzzles

22:51.137 --> 22:55.039
and metaphor. Such as this one:
"Those who heard

22:55.041 --> 22:57.074
"the silent voice of the Master

22:57.076 --> 22:59.076
fell dumbstruck."

22:59.078 --> 23:02.046
- "Silent voice"?
Maybe that's like

23:02.048 --> 23:05.316
the weird hum
that took out the SEALs.

23:05.318 --> 23:07.385
- What? What hum?

23:07.387 --> 23:10.421
- It's hard to explain.
When I was down--

23:10.423 --> 23:12.890
- By definition,
a hum is not silent.

23:12.892 --> 23:14.692
But bottom line,
is there anything in here

23:14.694 --> 23:16.494
that tells us
how to destroy the Master?

23:16.496 --> 23:19.397
- Not with clarity, but
it does mention his destruction

23:19.399 --> 23:22.199
in several places.
Well, for example:

23:22.201 --> 23:25.369
"When the Face of God
shineth upon him,

23:25.371 --> 23:27.738
his essence is destroyed."

23:27.740 --> 23:32.176
- Good. All we have to do
is find the face of God.

23:32.178 --> 23:34.845
- You missing
the metaphor there, Doc?

23:34.847 --> 23:38.115
- Three weeks ago, you didn't
believe<i> strigoi</i> existed,

23:38.117 --> 23:41.719
because I didn't explain them in
scientific terms. How is this different?

23:41.721 --> 23:43.220
- We're not going
to win this war

23:43.222 --> 23:46.290
by deciphering a magic spell.

23:46.292 --> 23:48.793
- Do you think these scholars
made all this up?

23:48.795 --> 23:51.061
No! They witnessed
a real event!

23:51.063 --> 23:54.932
We just don't know what it was. - Well, it
sounds like they're talking about sunlight.

23:54.934 --> 23:57.468
But we know that doesn't work.
- I disagree.

23:57.470 --> 23:58.636
The sun burned him.

23:58.638 --> 24:01.439
Perhaps a longer exposure

24:01.441 --> 24:04.275
would have, uh--
- Does it say that in the<i> Lumen?</i>

24:04.277 --> 24:06.877
- No. In fact, it states

24:06.879 --> 24:08.813
that this event
must take place

24:08.815 --> 24:12.216
during an occultation.
- We just had an eclipse.

24:12.218 --> 24:14.618
When's the next one?
- Yeah, I looked it up.

24:14.620 --> 24:19.023
For New York City,
it's April 8, 2024.

24:24.397 --> 24:26.397
- What's your take, Fet?

24:27.834 --> 24:29.967
- It's not a clear-cut

24:29.969 --> 24:33.737
recipe for success, but, um...

24:33.739 --> 24:35.573
...I think the professor
will figure it out.

24:35.575 --> 24:38.275
- The Master went
to extraordinary lengths

24:38.277 --> 24:40.911
to keep the<i> Lumen</i>
out of our hands.

24:40.913 --> 24:43.314
That alone tells us
it's valuable.

24:45.151 --> 24:48.018
- If you say so.

24:50.289 --> 24:53.023
<i> - Move. Clear!</i>
(fast beeping)

24:53.025 --> 24:56.093
(gunshot)
- After all the resources

24:56.095 --> 24:58.128
I've poured into this project,

24:58.130 --> 25:00.731
this is what you bring me?

25:02.268 --> 25:05.603
- Every iteration
of this substance has triggered

25:05.605 --> 25:08.606
convulsions,
heart failure, catatonia.

25:08.608 --> 25:12.176
Not one subject improved. All
of them had to be terminated.

25:12.178 --> 25:15.379
- I've given your people
unlimited funding, security,

25:15.381 --> 25:17.314
the best food
and housing available.

25:17.316 --> 25:19.617
You have a chance
to save the world.

25:19.619 --> 25:21.619
What's the problem here?

25:21.621 --> 25:25.189
- The problem is that money
cannot change biology.

25:25.191 --> 25:27.157
- I know this works!

25:27.159 --> 25:31.228
I've seen it work.
- You've seen it work?

25:31.230 --> 25:33.998
Well, if you've seen it work,
show me the evidence.

25:34.000 --> 25:37.234
- No. Your job is to provide me
with the evidence!

25:37.236 --> 25:41.038
- There is none!
<i>Strigoi</i> blood is flat-out

25:41.040 --> 25:43.474
toxic to human beings. Period.

25:45.211 --> 25:48.979
This woman, this patient, came
to your Freedom Center for help.

25:48.981 --> 25:51.382
Yes, we told her
the treatment was experimental,

25:51.384 --> 25:54.385
but we didn't tell her it might
end with a bullet in the brain.

25:55.888 --> 25:59.356
I won't do this anymore,
Mr. Palmer.

25:59.358 --> 26:01.725
Goodbye.

26:01.727 --> 26:04.828
♪♪♪

26:04.830 --> 26:06.897
(Palmer sighs.)

26:20.680 --> 26:23.280
- The professor tells me
you lost your son...

26:25.685 --> 26:28.519
...and that your companion
was killed.

26:30.957 --> 26:32.556
Yet you waited
all this time

26:32.558 --> 26:35.092
to come here
and share the tragic news.

26:35.094 --> 26:37.728
What prompted you to come now?

26:37.730 --> 26:39.964
- Took me a while
to find them.

26:39.966 --> 26:41.932
- Suddenly, you had
the epiphany to ask

26:41.934 --> 26:44.768
this Faraldo woman
where they were.

26:44.770 --> 26:47.371
I can see how it would take
a week to think of that.

26:47.373 --> 26:48.906
(distant explosions)

26:48.908 --> 26:52.376
- I wasn't ready
to talk about it.

26:52.378 --> 26:55.312
If you were capable of feelings,
you'd understand.

26:55.314 --> 26:59.383
- I exist free of the Master's leash. I've
experienced the same emotions as you.

26:59.385 --> 27:01.952
- Oh, right, you're half human.
I've been meaning to ask you

27:01.954 --> 27:03.754
about that.
How does that work?

27:03.756 --> 27:06.390
<i> Strigoi</i> don't have
plumbing for procreation.

27:06.392 --> 27:09.226
Did your mom go to a fertility
clinic for the undead?

27:12.732 --> 27:16.734
- Does it give you
pleasure to bait me?

27:16.736 --> 27:18.669
Or are you simply trying
to distract me

27:18.671 --> 27:20.604
from discovering
your true purpose here?

27:20.606 --> 27:24.341
- I was just trying
to figure you out.

27:24.343 --> 27:27.578
You're... half human

27:27.580 --> 27:29.413
who feeds on people,

27:29.415 --> 27:32.983
but you've thrown your lot in
with a<i> strigoi</i> hunter.

27:32.985 --> 27:35.386
I mean, don't tell me
you believe in that magic book.

27:38.357 --> 27:41.325
- You ridicule the<i> Lumen,</i>

27:41.327 --> 27:44.094
yet you take
a keen interest in it.

27:46.032 --> 27:49.433
- I like good fiction.

27:52.138 --> 27:54.338
- I've lived
a long time, Doctor.

27:56.308 --> 27:59.376
I saw Emperor Domitian
slain by his own court.

27:59.378 --> 28:02.279
I witnessed
Giuliano Medici's murder

28:02.281 --> 28:04.314
during Easter services
and watched

28:04.316 --> 28:08.118
the Borgias
strangle their own.

28:08.120 --> 28:10.487
Over the centuries,

28:10.489 --> 28:13.824
I've developed a keen nose
for treachery, so

28:13.826 --> 28:17.027
I must wonder,

28:17.029 --> 28:20.164
what's the real reason
you're here?

28:20.166 --> 28:22.399
♪♪♪

28:26.539 --> 28:30.374
- It's funny, I was wondering
the same thing about you.

28:54.500 --> 28:58.268
- The whole thing
was so random.

28:58.270 --> 29:01.171
- There's nothing random
about it.

29:01.173 --> 29:04.108
You want to know what caused
this plague? Overpopulation.

29:04.110 --> 29:06.410
It was only a matter of time
before a virus mutated

29:06.412 --> 29:08.512
into something that would
take out the human race.

29:10.382 --> 29:12.349
If you ask me...

29:14.253 --> 29:16.754
...we deserved it.

29:16.756 --> 29:18.522
(clinking noise)
- You hear that?

29:18.524 --> 29:22.059
- Someone's here.
- Check.

29:22.061 --> 29:24.862
Come on.

29:24.864 --> 29:28.532
(footsteps)

29:32.138 --> 29:34.404
Jesus, Dutch!

29:34.406 --> 29:36.473
You scared
the shit out of us!

29:38.611 --> 29:40.944
You OK?

29:40.946 --> 29:43.480
Glad to see you made it back.
- No thanks to you.

29:43.482 --> 29:46.550
- Was I supposed to do? Die with you?
- Do I look dead?!

29:46.552 --> 29:48.318
(distant gunfire)

29:53.058 --> 29:56.727
- What are you doing, Dutch?
- Taking my fair share.

29:59.431 --> 30:01.665
Hold still. Come here.
- Stop screwing around.

30:01.667 --> 30:05.102
Look, I know you're pissed,
but this isn't cool.

30:05.104 --> 30:06.970
You don't see shit!

30:06.972 --> 30:08.839
(squelching sounds)
- Oh my God!

30:08.841 --> 30:11.041
- Oh, Christ!
- No!

30:12.311 --> 30:14.144
Oh no, no, no, no!
No, no, no, no!

30:14.146 --> 30:16.180
This can't happen to me!
- What should we do?

30:16.182 --> 30:19.449
- The only cure is "headectomy." -
You want us to cut off his head?!

30:19.451 --> 30:22.186
- If you don't, he'll turn
and he'll come after you.

30:22.188 --> 30:24.788
But I'm not gonna do it.
He's your problem.

30:24.790 --> 30:28.358
- You can't leave us here with him!
- Great. Thanks, Dutch.

30:28.360 --> 30:30.727
She doesn't give
a shit about us.

30:33.165 --> 30:36.200
She only cares about--
(woman screaming)

30:42.007 --> 30:44.007
- There.

30:44.009 --> 30:46.009
It's done.

30:46.011 --> 30:49.279
(woman crying)

30:53.519 --> 30:55.519
- Good?

30:55.521 --> 30:58.055
- It's the first decent food
I've had in weeks.

30:58.057 --> 31:01.024
- This club used to serve food
to its members.

31:01.026 --> 31:02.993
The kitchen is
well provisioned.

31:02.995 --> 31:05.128
- I'll have to come
by here more often.

31:07.032 --> 31:09.867
I've been thinking about what
you said before, about Zack.

31:09.869 --> 31:12.870
Even if the Master
is keeping him alive

31:12.872 --> 31:16.340
just to get to me,
I could still get him back.

31:16.342 --> 31:20.143
- I suppose there's
a small chance. I know

31:20.145 --> 31:21.979
that's not what you want
to hear, but--

31:21.981 --> 31:24.047
- Any chance is better
than no chance.

31:24.049 --> 31:25.749
And if I can
get that opportunity--

31:25.751 --> 31:29.386
- Then you should take it.
But you must beware.

31:29.388 --> 31:31.688
The Master knows your desire.

31:31.690 --> 31:34.391
You could be playing
right into his hands.

31:34.393 --> 31:36.660
- Of course.

31:38.230 --> 31:41.231
- I'm very fond of Zack.
Should an opportunity

31:41.233 --> 31:43.400
to rescue him arise,

31:43.402 --> 31:46.236
I'll do what I can
to assist you.

31:48.173 --> 31:51.742
- I appreciate that.
- And our best hope of creating

31:51.744 --> 31:54.111
that opportunity
is the<i> Lumen.</i>

31:54.113 --> 31:56.947
It will provide me the key
to destroying the Master.

31:56.949 --> 31:58.949
And when I do,

31:58.951 --> 32:01.084
perhaps we can
recover your boy.

32:01.086 --> 32:03.253
(door opening)

32:03.255 --> 32:06.857
- Professor, just got a message
through Faraldo's people.

32:06.859 --> 32:09.259
Rudyard Fonescu wants
to meet with you.

32:09.261 --> 32:11.194
- Who?

32:11.196 --> 32:14.197
- For 40 years he possessed
the<i> Lumen.</i>

32:14.199 --> 32:16.199
Did he say where and when?

32:16.201 --> 32:18.235
- West 15th under the High Line,
an hour.

32:18.237 --> 32:21.438
- Then we should go now.
- I suppose I better--

32:21.440 --> 32:23.640
- No, no. Stay. Help yourself
to some more stew.

32:33.953 --> 32:36.586
- I thought Rudyard Fonescu

32:36.588 --> 32:38.588
took his money and ran.

32:38.590 --> 32:40.924
What's he doing
still kicking around New York?

32:40.926 --> 32:43.493
- Hopefully,
he has further information

32:43.495 --> 32:46.330
about the<i> Lumen</i> to sell.
- Or we could be walking

32:46.332 --> 32:48.131
into an ambush.

32:48.133 --> 32:51.168
Get back!

32:51.170 --> 32:54.104
- (distant woman):
Get out of here! Go!

32:54.106 --> 32:56.306
(vehicle doors closing)

33:09.188 --> 33:10.620
- Put down the gun.

33:10.622 --> 33:13.423
Let's hear
what he has to say.

33:16.829 --> 33:19.129
- Apologies for
the Fonescu ruse,

33:19.131 --> 33:21.598
but I know you wouldn't
come otherwise.

33:23.302 --> 33:26.803
- What do you want, Eldritch?
- I want to strike a deal.

33:26.805 --> 33:29.206
- Go on.

33:31.210 --> 33:34.778
- I am willing to remove
myself from the game,

33:34.780 --> 33:36.813
leave New York,

33:36.815 --> 33:39.983
withdraw all my support
for the Master.

33:39.985 --> 33:42.319
- You'll forgive my disbelief.

33:42.321 --> 33:45.455
- Oh, I am still essential
to the Master.

33:45.457 --> 33:48.191
And there are still
a few critical moves to be made,

33:48.193 --> 33:51.461
which require my participation
if they are to succeed.

33:51.463 --> 33:54.031
If I abandon
the Master,

33:54.033 --> 33:55.866
you will gain

33:55.868 --> 33:57.868
a massive advantage
over him.

33:57.870 --> 33:59.870
For that,

33:59.872 --> 34:01.905
I want something
in return.

34:01.907 --> 34:05.709
- And what would that be?
- The formula.

34:05.711 --> 34:08.578
- What formula?

34:10.382 --> 34:12.115
- For the white.

34:13.519 --> 34:17.354
Abraham, you're a very,
very old man.

34:17.356 --> 34:19.489
There is only one explanation

34:19.491 --> 34:22.526
for your extraordinary vigor.

34:22.528 --> 34:24.494
<i> Strigoi</i> blood.

34:24.496 --> 34:27.164
You've found a way
to refine it, haven't you,

34:27.166 --> 34:29.199
so you can remain human
yet benefit

34:29.201 --> 34:31.201
from its restorative effects.

34:31.203 --> 34:34.004
- That's insane.

34:34.006 --> 34:36.339
- And what if I have?

34:36.341 --> 34:38.675
- Give me the formula;

34:38.677 --> 34:42.345
I will walk away forever
leaving the Master exposed.

34:42.347 --> 34:44.247
You can save this city

34:44.249 --> 34:46.583
and the human race.
Your life's quest

34:46.585 --> 34:49.386
will come
to a successful end.

34:49.388 --> 34:51.388
It costs you nothing.

34:51.390 --> 34:53.690
You have everything to gain.

34:53.692 --> 34:57.194
Do we have a deal?

35:03.902 --> 35:07.771
- I remember another handshake
years ago

35:07.773 --> 35:10.474
in Vienna

35:10.476 --> 35:13.043
and the betrayal
that followed.

35:14.213 --> 35:17.280
- Yes, I betrayed you.

35:17.282 --> 35:20.484
Now, I want
to make amends.

35:20.486 --> 35:24.321
I hope it's not too late
for redemption.

35:24.323 --> 35:26.123
- You may call it redemption,

35:26.125 --> 35:28.425
but I have another word
for it --

35:28.427 --> 35:30.127
treachery.

35:30.129 --> 35:33.597
I have the<i> Lumen</i>
and I have the white.

35:33.599 --> 35:35.465
What do you have?

35:35.467 --> 35:38.635
- I have the power
to alter the outcome.

35:40.072 --> 35:43.707
- You can go to hell, Eldritch,
where you belong.

36:06.031 --> 36:11.001
- So, uh, how long
you been taking that stuff?

36:11.003 --> 36:13.603
<i> Strigoi</i> blood.

36:13.605 --> 36:15.505
- Off and on

36:15.507 --> 36:17.574
for 41 years.

36:19.945 --> 36:22.279
- How'd you figure out a way

36:22.281 --> 36:24.781
to keep it from turning you
full muncher?

36:24.783 --> 36:26.716
- Edvard Frankel,

36:26.718 --> 36:30.187
an old<i> strigoi</i> hunter
I knew in Vienna, taught me

36:30.189 --> 36:32.556
the formula.
It's been handed down

36:32.558 --> 36:36.059
among selected alchemists
since the third century.

36:36.061 --> 36:39.996
- And what? You're gonna live
forever like Quinlan?

36:39.998 --> 36:43.166
- No. The white will extend
my life a few more years,

36:43.168 --> 36:45.368
allow me to continue the fight.

36:45.370 --> 36:48.872
But Palmer's mistaken.

36:48.874 --> 36:52.309
It will not give him
eternal life.

36:54.379 --> 36:56.379
- No need to tell him that.

36:56.381 --> 36:58.315
Better he thinks otherwise.

36:58.317 --> 37:00.283
We certainly can't trust him.

37:01.587 --> 37:03.753
- But we may be able

37:03.755 --> 37:06.456
to manipulate him.

37:10.996 --> 37:12.996
♪♪♪

37:33.118 --> 37:35.418
- I made you some food.

37:35.420 --> 37:37.420
- Cool.

37:37.422 --> 37:39.456
Can you put it
on the table for me?

37:39.458 --> 37:41.625
- Yeah.

37:48.800 --> 37:52.369
You've been reading.
- Not much else to do.

37:52.371 --> 37:54.537
(slow fan noise)
- Would you like me

37:54.539 --> 37:57.207
to read with you?
- Maybe later.

37:57.209 --> 37:59.342
I'm tired.

38:00.979 --> 38:03.046
- It's good to eat.

38:14.593 --> 38:17.127
So, when can I go
to see Dad?

38:18.463 --> 38:21.865
- Soon.
- Your new favorite word.

38:25.470 --> 38:27.470
- I know it is difficult,

38:27.472 --> 38:30.874
but we must be patient.

38:35.914 --> 38:38.181
(sound of beating pulse)

38:44.256 --> 38:46.456
(The sound of the pulse stops.)

38:46.458 --> 38:48.925
(slow fan noise)

38:55.434 --> 38:57.767
- I wanna go to bed.

38:57.769 --> 38:59.769
Good night.

39:01.540 --> 39:05.342
- Good night, my dear one.

39:14.720 --> 39:17.587
(footsteps retreating)

39:24.363 --> 39:26.863
(distant door opening
and closing)

39:59.898 --> 40:02.432
(chain clanking)

40:02.434 --> 40:05.235
(steady thumping)

40:07.272 --> 40:10.707
(squelching)

40:10.709 --> 40:13.276
(steady pumping)

40:17.883 --> 40:19.482
- Mom?

40:21.853 --> 40:23.920
(growling)

40:23.922 --> 40:26.456
(suspenseful music)
(Zack gasping)

40:26.458 --> 40:27.524
- Zack!

40:27.526 --> 40:29.526
(Zack gasping for breath)

40:32.864 --> 40:35.231
